div.p:
See Life ofW. Paterson, byS. Bannister (Edinburgh, 1858);
                    Paterson⅛ Works, 3 vols., by S. Bannister (London, 1859);
                    The Birthplace and Parentage of W. Paterson, by W. Pagan
                    (Edinburgh, 1865). The brilliant account in the fifth volume of Macaulay’s History is incorrect and misleading. That in Burton’s Hist, of Scotland (vol. viii. ch. 84) is much truer. A list
                    of a number of fugitive writings on Paterson will be found in Poole's Maa. Index. (F. WA.)
